I'm not finding this in a grep? Where is it defined. Would we ever not want openpower-dump-collection enabled? This is the openpower-debug-collector recipe so seems like it would just be the default.
You are right Andrew. There is a phal flag downstream that enables openpower-dump-collection. Will get that commit pushed to upstream review before this commit.

openpower-dump-collection is enabled if phal MACHINE_FEATURES flag is enabled. please see the base commit from Dhruv in this chain of commits.
https://gerrit.openbmc.org/c/openbmc/openbmc/+/42327/29/meta-openpower/recipes-phosphor/debug/openpower-debug-collector_git.bb
